From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 13:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/N] Nix installer fixes (any Nix-built install)

Under any Nix install (NixOS, Nix-on-Ubuntu, Nix-on-macOS), the
pai-nix wrapper provides `pai` on PATH directly — the upstream
installer must not inject shell aliases, show macOS-specific prompts,
or display incorrect launch instructions. Linux + macOS platform
distinctions still apply orthogonally to the Nix-install distinction
(macOS has launchd + menu bar; Linux does not).

Changes:
- Guard shell alias injection with the Nix-install marker (initially
  NIX_STORE; corrected to PAI_NIX_INSTALL by patch 0005 — see note
  below).
- Show `pai` instead of `source ~/.zshrc && pai` under any Nix
  install.
- Skip macOS menu bar app prompt on Linux (`process.platform`
  check, not Nix-related).
- Use platform-appropriate Pulse wording on Linux (same).
- Skip launchd plist validation on Linux (same).
- Skip shell alias validation under any Nix install.
- Wait 5 seconds before process.exit so user can read summary (only
  outside Nix-built installs; Nix wrapper keeps the terminal open).
- Fix Electron GUI: extend auto-close from 3s to 30s so user can
  read summary.
- Fix Electron GUI: show `pai` instead of `source ~/.zshrc && pai`.
- Fix Electron GUI: window is created but hidden behind other
  windows or on another virtual desktop, leading users to think the
  GUI never opened. Show on did-finish-load, center on primary
  display, briefly raise to top, and log lifecycle events so
  failures are visible instead of silent.

Note: this patch's hunks gate on `process.env.NIX_STORE`. NIX_STORE
is build-time-only — it is empty in user-shell runtime. Patch 0005
corrects every gate to `process.env.PAI_NIX_INSTALL`, the explicit
runtime marker the pai-nix wrapper exports. Intermediate state
(after 0004 but before 0005) has the broken gate; only the final
post-0005 state is correct.

